column13: General purpose, good for aerobatics. Zero lift at 0 AoA. Drag increases sharply past cruise AoA.
Common general aviation profile, good lift. Lift at 0 AoA (~0.25).
Similar to 2412, but earlier camber provides slightly higher lift at higher AoA.
Higher thickness, good for structures or slower flight. More lift at lower speeds.
Designed for low drag (laminar flow) over a narrow Cl range (the 'bucket'). Sensitive to surface roughness, stall can be abrupt.
Very low drag at near-zero lift coefficients. Good for high-speed, long-endurance cruise. Stall can be abrupt.
